 ```
 
+### git output must not leak into generated scripts
+
+Some git wrappers found on `PATH` write progress to stdout even for
+`git --quiet`. Since `antidote-script`'s stdout *is* the generated plugin
+script, that stray text would corrupt it. It gets routed to stderr instead, so
+real diagnostics stay visible.
+
+```zsh
+% function git { [[ "$1" = "clone" ]] && print 'GITWRAPPER progress on stdout'; mockgit "$@" }
+% antidote-script --kind zsh fakeuser/fakerepo 2>/dev/null | grep 'GITWRAPPER' #=> --exit 1
+% antidote-script --kind zsh fakeuser/fakerepo 2>/dev/null | subenv ANTIDOTE_HOME
+fpath+=( "$ANTIDOTE_HOME/fakeuser/fakerepo" )
+source "$ANTIDOTE_HOME/fakeuser/fakerepo/fakerepo.plugin.zsh"
+% function git { mockgit "$@" }
+%
+```
+
